{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SnowCappingRunoff",
        "description": "Solid and liquid runoff from snow capping for snow-covered surfaces, following Oleson et al. (2010, CLM Tech Note Ch. 5) Eqs. 5.153-5.154. When the model has reached its prescribed maximum snow water equivalent, additional precipitation and atmospheric deposition cannot accumulate on the snowpack and is shed to the surface as `snow capping runoff` — the solid stream comes from solid precipitation plus frost (Eq. 5.153) and the liquid stream from liquid precipitation plus dew (Eq. 5.154). Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/hydrology.jl:823 (`SnowCappingRunoff` @component). Parameterized as observed-only: q_grnd_ice, q_grnd_liq, q_frost, q_dew are inputs (parameters); q_snwcp_ice and q_snwcp_liq are algebraic outputs.",
        "tags": [
            "urban_canopy",
            "hydrology",
            "snow",
            "runoff",
            "observed-only",
            "clmu"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-06T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (mdl-rhiv)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Oleson, K. W., et al. (2010). Technical Description of version 4.0 of the Community Land Model (CLM). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-478+STR. Chapter 5, Section 5.5 (Snow capping runoff), Eqs. 5.153-5.154, p. 146."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "SnowCappingRunoff": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/hydrology.jl:823\nUpstream `SnowCappingRunoff` is an MTK `@component` whose four inputs (q_grnd_ice, q_grnd_liq, q_frost, q_dew) are `@parameters` and whose two outputs (q_snwcp_ice, q_snwcp_liq) are time-indexed `@variables` with algebraic-only equations (no derivatives). Identical equation structure preserved here.\n\nThe upstream component declares no `@constants` — all four inputs are user-facing fluxes (precipitation, frost, dew rates) with no embedded physical constants. The two outputs are decoupled: q_snwcp_ice depends only on the ice/frost pair and q_snwcp_liq depends only on the liq/dew pair, so the component is two independent additive identities sharing a name. Tests exploit this by sweeping each branch independently.\n\nObservability classification: this component is functionally observed-only — every output variable is given by a single algebraic equation (a two-term sum) in terms of the parameters (and the `(t)` time index has no role since there is no derivative). Test scenarios use `time_span: [0, 1]` and sample at t=0 to mirror the convention used by the other observed-only ESM files in this rig (impervious_runoff.esm, soil_water_content_calc.esm, etc.).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); each equation is a single addition, so roundoff is at the IEEE-754 ULP level (~1e-16). 1e-9 leaves comfortable headroom above ULP roundoff and matches the convention used by sibling observed-only files (soil_water_content_calc.esm uses 1e-9 for analogous algebraic-sum equations). Tighter `abs: 1e-12` is asserted on outputs that are exactly zero by construction so the assertion does not silently accept a stuck-at-1e-3 regression."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-9
            },
            "variables": {
                "q_grnd_ice": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Solid precipitation reaching surface"
                },
                "q_grnd_liq": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Liquid precipitation reaching surface"
                },
                "q_frost": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Frost rate (atmospheric water vapor deposition as ice on snow surface)"
                },
                "q_dew": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Dew rate (atmospheric water vapor condensation as liquid on snow surface)"
                },
                "q_snwcp_ice": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Solid runoff from snow capping (Oleson Eq. 5.153): q_grnd_ice + q_frost"
                },
                "q_snwcp_liq": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Liquid runoff from snow capping (Oleson Eq. 5.154): q_grnd_liq + q_dew"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "q_snwcp_ice",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": ["q_grnd_ice", "q_frost"]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "q_snwcp_liq",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": ["q_grnd_liq", "q_dew"]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "upstream_equation_verification",
                    "description": "Reproduces upstream `SnowCappingRunoff - Equation Verification` test (UrbanCanopy.jl test/hydrology_test.jl:551). Inputs: q_grnd_ice = 0.001, q_frost = 0.0005, q_grnd_liq = 0.002, q_dew = 0.0003. q_snwcp_ice = 0.001 + 0.0005 = 0.0015; q_snwcp_liq = 0.002 + 0.0003 = 0.0023. Anchors fidelity to the upstream Julia component at the same parameter values.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.001,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.002,
                        "q_frost": 0.0005,
                        "q_dew": 0.0003
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0015 },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0023 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "all_zero_inputs",
                    "description": "Bone-dry / zero-flux limit: no precipitation, no frost, no dew. Both runoff streams must be exactly zero — exercises the additive-zero limit of Eqs. 5.153-5.154.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.0,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_dew": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "snowfall_only_no_frost",
                    "description": "Solid precipitation with no frost (clear-sky snowfall, no surface deposition). q_snwcp_ice = q_grnd_ice = 0.005; q_snwcp_liq = 0 (no rain, no dew). Exercises the q_grnd_ice-only branch of Eq. 5.153 and confirms the liquid stream is decoupled from the solid stream.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.005,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_dew": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.005 },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "frost_only_no_snow",
                    "description": "Frost deposition with no solid precipitation (e.g. clear cold night, surface vapor flux freezes onto snow surface). q_snwcp_ice = q_frost = 0.0008; q_snwcp_liq = 0. Exercises the q_frost-only branch of Eq. 5.153 — frost contributes to the same solid runoff stream as snowfall.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.0,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0008,
                        "q_dew": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0008 },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "rainfall_only_no_dew",
                    "description": "Liquid precipitation with no dew (e.g. rain on saturated snowpack). q_snwcp_ice = 0; q_snwcp_liq = q_grnd_liq = 0.003. Exercises the q_grnd_liq-only branch of Eq. 5.154 and confirms the solid stream is decoupled.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.0,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.003,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_dew": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.003 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dew_only_no_rain",
                    "description": "Dew deposition with no liquid precipitation (humid cold morning, vapor condenses on snow but doesn't freeze). q_snwcp_ice = 0; q_snwcp_liq = q_dew = 0.0004. Exercises the q_dew-only branch of Eq. 5.154 — dew feeds the liquid runoff stream alongside rainfall.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.0,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_dew": 0.0004
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0004 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "heavy_snowstorm",
                    "description": "Heavy snowstorm with concurrent frost (cold, humid storm conditions). q_grnd_ice = 0.02, q_frost = 0.001 → q_snwcp_ice = 0.021. Negligible liquid (q_grnd_liq = q_dew = 0). Stress-tests the high-flux solid regime where snowfall dominates and frost is a small concurrent contribution.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.02,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.001,
                        "q_dew": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.021 },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "rain_on_snow_with_dew",
                    "description": "Rain-on-snow event with concurrent dew (warm front over snowpack, humid). q_grnd_liq = 0.015, q_dew = 0.0002 → q_snwcp_liq = 0.0152. Negligible solid (q_grnd_ice = q_frost = 0). Stress-tests the high-flux liquid regime where rainfall dominates and dew is a small concurrent contribution.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.0,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.015,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_dew": 0.0002
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0152 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "mixed_phase_storm",
                    "description": "Mixed-phase storm (sleet/wet snow, transitional temperature) with both phases of precipitation and both surface deposition modes. q_grnd_ice = 0.004, q_frost = 0.0002, q_grnd_liq = 0.006, q_dew = 0.0001. q_snwcp_ice = 0.0042; q_snwcp_liq = 0.0061. Exercises the full four-input regime simultaneously and confirms the two output streams remain orthogonal (each independent of the other branch's inputs).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.004,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.006,
                        "q_frost": 0.0002,
                        "q_dew": 0.0001
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0042 },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0061 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "branch_independence",
                    "description": "Cross-coupling sanity check: very large solid-side inputs and zero liquid-side inputs. q_grnd_ice = 1.0, q_frost = 0.5 → q_snwcp_ice = 1.5 (huge); q_grnd_liq = q_dew = 0 → q_snwcp_liq must remain exactly 0. Confirms the two branches do not leak into each other through any spurious coupling — solid mass on one channel cannot show up as liquid runoff on the other.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 1.0,
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.5,
                        "q_dew": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.5 },
                        { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "ice_runoff_vs_snowfall_with_frost",
                    "description": "Sweep solid precipitation rate q_grnd_ice across a typical CLMU range with a small fixed frost contribution (q_frost = 0.0005 kg/(m^2*s)). q_snwcp_ice = q_grnd_ice + 0.0005 — a unit-slope line offset by the frost term, surfacing Eq. 5.153 directly. Liquid-side inputs held at zero so the liquid stream is identically zero across the sweep.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "q_grnd_liq": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0005,
                        "q_dew": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "q_grnd_ice",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 0.02, "count": 21, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "q_snwcp_ice_curve",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "q_snwcp_ice vs q_grnd_ice (frost = 0.0005): unit-slope line offset by the frost term per Eq. 5.153.",
                            "x": { "variable": "q_grnd_ice", "label": "q_grnd_ice (kg/(m^2*s))" },
                            "y": { "variable": "q_snwcp_ice", "label": "q_snwcp_ice (kg/(m^2*s))" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "liq_runoff_phase_partition",
                    "description": "Joint sweep over q_grnd_liq and q_dew at fixed solid-side zero. Surfaces the perfectly additive plane q_snwcp_liq = q_grnd_liq + q_dew (Eq. 5.154) — iso-runoff contours are 45-degree lines in the (q_grnd_liq, q_dew) plane. Visualizes the equal-weighting between the two liquid sources (rain and dew contribute identically per unit flux).",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "q_grnd_ice": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "q_grnd_liq",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 0.01, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "q_dew",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 0.001, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "q_snwcp_liq_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "q_snwcp_liq as a function of liquid precipitation and dew rates: planar additive surface per Eq. 5.154.",
                            "x": { "variable": "q_grnd_liq", "label": "q_grnd_liq (kg/(m^2*s))" },
                            "y": { "variable": "q_dew",      "label": "q_dew (kg/(m^2*s))" },
                            "value": { "variable": "q_snwcp_liq", "reduce": "final" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
